    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-01T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857B46</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-01T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1916, 3 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2873. Department is informed that British steamer <hi rend="italic"
                        >Berwindvale</hi>, carrying four Americans, was torpedoed without warning on
                    March 16 off Bantry, Ireland. The vessel was apparently returning to the United
                    States for cargo.</p>
                <p>Please bring this to the attention of the German Government with request to be
                    informed whether this vessel was torpedoed by a submarine belonging to Germany
                    or her allies. It is expected that a prompt answer will be given.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
